        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">01</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">I&rsquo;m a Search Fund / ETA searcher in active search phase. How does my W-2 qualify?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Search Fund LLC W-2 income (typically $80K-$120K investor-funded base during 18-30 month search phase) qualifies under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.1-01/general-income-information" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01</a>. Where 2-year history exists, 24-month average applies. For early-search-phase searchers without 2-year Search Fund history, we document the Search Fund LLC formation, $350K-$500K investor capital commitment, and continuing-employment narrative.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">02</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">I&rsquo;m a Self-Funded Searcher without investor backing. How can I qualify during search?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Self-Funded Searchers during search phase commonly use Asset-Depletion Non-QM qualifying on personal liquid capital reserves amortized over 360 months as implied monthly income. A $1M liquid balance amortizes to roughly $2,800/month implied income. Useful when current W-2 / Schedule C income reduced or absent during search phase. Pricing carries 0.5-1% rate premium vs Conventional.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">03</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">I&rsquo;m an Independent Sponsor. How do management fees + carry qualify?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Independent Sponsor management fees + carry recognition events qualify under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.3-02/income-analysis-self-employed-borrowers" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">B3-3.3-02</a> (Schedule C) or <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.4-02/analyzing-returns-partnership-or-s-corporation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">B3-3.4-02</a> (S-corp / partnership) with 24-month averaging plus Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks. Lumpy carry recognition is smoothed by the 24-month average. We document the active portfolio of in-flight transactions, management fee recurring structure, and carry vesting schedule.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">04</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">Should I close my mortgage BEFORE or AFTER the acquisition?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Generally BEFORE if feasible. BEFORE: uses prior W-2 / Schedule C history (corporate, MBA stipend, search fund W-2) without SBA personal guarantee in DTI calculation; locks in qualifying capacity at established income level. AFTER: requires 12-24 months of post-acquisition operating history at acquired company for B3-3.4-02 K-1 documentation. The acquisition-close window itself is the lowest-qualifying period &mdash; new-employment status at acquired company. We coordinate timing strategically.</div>
