 W-2 and corporate pre-search W-2, B3-3.3-02 self-employed Schedule C analysis with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks for Independent Sponsors, B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corporation analysis for post-acquisition owner-CEO K-1 with substantial entity-level Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks recovering goodwill amortization and asset step-up depreciation. Conventional Conforming, Conventional Jumbo, Conventional Super-Jumbo, S-Corp Self-Employed, Schedule C + Form 1084, Bank Statement Non-QM, Asset-Depletion Non-QM (Self-Funded Searcher during search), and SBA 7(a) coordination loan program options. CRITICAL: SBA 7(a) personal guarantee creates contingent liability factoring into mortgage underwriting DTI calculation. Sequencing residential mortgage close BEFORE acquisition (using prior W-2 / Schedule C history without SBA personal guarantee) or AFTER 12-24 months of operating history at acquired company produces fundamentally different qualifying outcomes. Stanford Search Fund Study annual research from Stanford GSB Center for Entrepreneurial Studies tracks the asset class growth from 90 funds in 2013 to over 400 active funds in recent studies with investor returns averaging 35%+ IRR across multi-decade history. SBA 7(a) acquisition financing capacity expansion, Independent Sponsor model proliferation, PE-backed roll-up activity in lower-middle-market, boomer-owned SMB succession wave creating massive supply of acquisition targets, and Florida-specific tourism, marine, hospitality acquisition opportunities industry dynamics." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/professional-services/business-acquirers/">
